  <title>The Open University :Scottish Government&apos;s Saltire Scholarships; Supporting women into teaching in rural Malawi</title>
  <description>The Open University will develop the Saltire Scholarship scheme. This will provide local school-based access to a teaching career for women in rural areas of Malawi. The project will tackle two major problems in Malawian education: teacher shortage at levels leading to one of the highest pupil teacher ratios in the world; and a severe lack of women teachers in rural schools.Through this scholarship scheme, 500 women will receive training in their local community enabling them to progress onto formal teacher education programmes.</description>
